Controversial socialite and nightlife connoisseur, Mike Eze Nwalie Nwogu aka Pretty Mike revealed that people are willing to pay for him to pull stunts at their parties. The entertainer, who has gone viral severally for attending parties in weird manners, made this revelation at a recent event in Lagos. Mike, an actor and nightclub owner, is one of the celebrities people look out for at top events in Nigeria for his controversial entry. “I do have friends that tell me to come and pull stunts at their wedding, some people even want to pay me for it.   Omo Borty, Sydney Talker, others attend Abike Halima’s…     Umanu Elijah makes 2021 breakout film directors list     Don’t waste your life with temporary situations –…   - Advertisement - “It’s not something I just generate, I don’t repeat stunts. For example, as I’m talking to you now, I don’t have any stunts coming up in my head but it doesn’t mean something won’t come up next week. “I only do stunts at my very close friends’ parties, that’s what people need to understand. If you’re not my very close friend, I will not pull a stunt at your party because I hear people on social media say if he does that at my party I will throw him out, I’m not even coming to your party,” Pretty Mike said. He also added that pulling up at parties in weird ways is his pet project. “It’s like a pet project for me just as some people like to feed the poor, I like what I do.”